'''海洋低氧现象'''是由于人为活动<ref name="IUCN2019">{{Cite book|last=Laffoley|first=D|last2=Baxter|first2=JM|title=Ocean deoxygenation : everyone’s problem|date=2019|publisher=Gland|location=Switzerland|isbn=978-2-8317-2013-5|pages=562|url=https://portals.iucn.org/library/node/48892|access-date=2020-11-14|archive-date=2021-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210413170615/https://portals.iucn.org/library/node/48892|dead-url=no}}</ref>而导致的[[大洋|海洋]]氧含量降低的现象，这是[[温室气体|人为排放的二氧化碳]]<ref name="Stramma">{{Cite journal|title=Expanding Oxygen-Minimum Zones in the Tropical Oceans|last=Stramma|first=L|last2=Johnson|first2=GC|date=2008|journal=Science|issue=5876|doi=10.1126/science.1153847|volume=320|pages=655–658|last3=Printall|first3=J|last4=Mohrholz|first4=V}}</ref><ref name="Mora">{{Cite journal|title=Biotic and Human Vulnerability to Projected Changes in Ocean Biogeochemistry over the 21st Century|last=Mora|first=C|date=2013|journal=PLOS Biology|issue=10|doi=10.1371/journal.pbio.1001682|volume=11|page=e1001682|display-authors=etal}}</ref>和[[富营养化|富营养化]]日益严重造成的结果。主要表现为在沿海和河口[[缺氧|缺氧]]区域（或[[死亡区|死亡区]]）的数量不断增加，以及全球海洋中最低氧含量区域的扩大。海洋中氧含量的下降相当迅速，全球低氧海域以每年5.54%的速率增长<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Vaquer-Sunyer |first1=Raquel |last2=Duarte |first2=Carlos M. |title=Thresholds of hypoxia for marine biodiversity |journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences |date=2008-10-07 |volume=105 |issue=40 |pages=15452–15457 |doi=10.1073/pnas.0803833105}}</ref>，对所有[[好氧生物|有氧]][[海洋生物|海洋生物]]以及依赖海洋生物获取营养或生计的人们构成了威胁<ref>{{cite news |last1= |first1= |title=Oceans suffocating as huge dead zones quadruple since 1950, scientists warn |url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2018/jan/04/oceans-suffocating-dead-zones-oxygen-starved |accessdate=2020-11-14 |work=The Guardian |date=2018-01-04 |archive-date=2021-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210413015402/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2018/jan/04/oceans-suffocating-dead-zones-oxygen-starved |dead-url=no }}</ref>  <ref>{{cite news |author1=Niina Heikkinen, ClimateWire |first1= |title=Ocean's Oxygen Starts Running Low |url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/ocean-s-oxygen-starts-running-low/ |accessdate=2020-11-14 |work=Scientific American |date=2016-05-02 |language=en |archive-date=2021-02-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226071346/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/ocean-s-oxygen-starts-running-low/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Long |first1=Matthew C. |last2=Deutsch |first2=Curtis |last3=Ito |first3=Taka |title=Finding forced trends in oceanic oxygen: TRENDS IN DISSOLVED OXYGEN |journal=Global Biogeochemical Cycles |date=2016-02 |volume=30 |issue=2 |pages=381–397 |doi=10.1002/2015GB005310}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Guest post: How global warming is causing ocean oxygen levels to fall |url=https://www.carbonbrief.org/guest-post-how-global-warming-is-causing-ocean-oxygen-levels-to-fall |accessdate=2020-11-14 |work=Carbon Brief |date=2018-06-15 |language=en |archive-date=2021-02-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210204123358/https://www.carbonbrief.org/guest-post-how-global-warming-is-causing-ocean-oxygen-levels-to-fall |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

一般而言，水中[[溶解氧|溶解氧]]浓度小于2mg/L时，就被认为处于低氧状态<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Gray |first1=Js |last2=Wu |first2=Rs |last3=Or |first3=Yy |title=Effects of hypoxia and organic enrichment on the coastal marine environment |journal=Marine Ecology Progress Series |date=2002 |volume=238 |pages=249–279 |doi=10.3354/meps238249}}</ref>。可分为周期性低氧、季节性低氧和持续性低氧<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Diaz |first1=R. J. |last2=Rosenberg |first2=R. |title=Spreading Dead Zones and Consequences for Marine Ecosystems |journal=Science |date=2008-08-15 |volume=321 |issue=5891 |pages=926–929 |doi=10.1126/science.1156401}}</ref>。

当前[[波罗的海|波罗的海]]是全球最大的死亡区，20%的海域至少有40年一直处于缺氧状态<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Conley |first1=Daniel J. |last2=Humborg |first2=Christoph |last3=Rahm |first3=Lars |last4=Savchuk |first4=Oleg P. |last5=Wulff |first5=Fredrik |title=Hypoxia in the Baltic Sea and Basin-Scale Changes in Phosphorus Biogeochemistry |journal=Environmental Science & Technology |date=2002-12 |volume=36 |issue=24 |pages=5315–5320 |doi=10.1021/es025763w}}</ref>，而[[黑海|黑海]]在150-250米水层处有90%的海域出现低氧现象<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Diaz |first1=Robert J. |title=Overview of Hypoxia around the World |journal=Journal of Environmental Quality |date=2001-03 |volume=30 |issue=2 |pages=275–281 |doi=10.2134/jeq2001.302275x}}</ref>。
